<p>The <a href="https://royalinstitutephilosophy.org/">Royal Institute of Philosophy</a> recently announced the longlist of books being considered for the 2025 Nayef Al-Rodhan International Prize in Transdisciplinary Philosophy. <span id="more-54599"></span></p>
<p>The £20,000 prize recognizes &#8220;books that transcend academic boundaries&#8221; that &#8220;further&#8230; our understanding of the key challenges facing the world today&#8221; in areas such as the future of humanity, disruptive technologies, global governance, transcultural understanding, scientific innovation, human nature, and transdisciplinary methodologies.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b3b3b3;">.</span></p>
<p>The longlisted authors and books are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Manuel Almagro (2025), <em><a href="https://www.routledge.com/The-Rise-of-Polarization-Affects-Politics-and-Philosophy/Almagro/p/book/9781032509600">The Rise of Polarization: Affects, Politics, and Philosophy</a></em> (Routledge)</li>
<li>Jonathan Birch (2024), <em><a href="https://academic.oup.com/book/57949">The Edge of Sentience: Risk and Precaution in Humans, Other Animals, and AI</a></em> (Oxford University Press)</li>
<li>Peter Godfrey-Smith (2024), <em><a href="https://harpercollins.co.uk/products/living-on-earth-life-consciousness-and-the-making-of-the-natural-world-peter-godfrey-smith?variant=41733703270478">Living on Earth: Life, Consciousness and the Making of the Natural World</a></em> (William Collins)</li>
<li>Jules Holroyd (2025), <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/Oppressive-Praise-Jules-Holroyd/dp/019288316X"><em>Oppressive Praise</em></a> (Oxford University Press)</li>
<li>Adam Lovett (2024), <a href="https://www.pennpress.org/9781512825794/democratic-failures-and-the-ethics-of-democracy/"><em>Democratic Failures and the Ethics of Democracy</em></a> (University of Pennsylvania Press)</li>
<li>Alva Noë (2023), <a href="https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780691188812/the-entanglement"><em>The Entanglement: How Art and Philosophy Make Us What We Are</em></a> (Princeton University Press)</li>
<li>Prashant Parikh (2024), <a href="https://hackettpublishing.com/meaning-is-everywhere-language-artificial-intelligence-society"><em>Meaning Is Everywhere: Language, Artificial Intelligence, and Society</em></a> (Hackett Publishing Company)</li>
<li>Alan Thomas, Alfred Archer, and Bart Engelen (2024), <a href="https://global.oup.com/academic/product/extravagance-and-misery-9780197781722?cc=gb&amp;lang=en&amp;"><em>Extravagance and Misery: The Emotional Regime of Market Societies</em></a> (Oxford University Press)</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class=" wp-image-54600 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist.png" alt="" width="701" height="525" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist.png 1089w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist-300x225.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist-1024x767.png 1024w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist-768x575.png 768w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/transdisciplinary-book-prize-2025-longlist-400x300.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px" /></p>
<p>The judging panel is chaired by <a href="https://www.constantinesandis.com/about">Constantine Sandis</a> (<a href="https://www.lexacademic.com/">Lex Academic</a>, Hertfordshire), and includes <a href="https://www.birmingham.ac.uk/staff/profiles/philosophy/bortolotti-lisa">Lisa Bortolotti</a> (Birmingham), <a href="https://www.polis.cam.ac.uk/Staff_and_Students/head-of-department">Jude Browne</a> (Cambridge), <a href="https://www.cacuccilab.net/cacucci-lab-team">Francesca Cacucci</a> (UCL), <a href="https://www.arch.ox.ac.uk/people/malafouris-lambros">Lambros Malafouris</a> (Oxford), <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alexis-papazoglou-63b666187/?originalSubdomain=uk">Alexis Papazoglou</a> (LSE), and <a href="https://research.london.ac.uk/institute-ip/staff/26/professor-barry-c-smith/">Barry Smith</a> (Institute of Philosophy, London).</p>
<p>The prize is named for and funded by <a href="http://www.sustainablehistory.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nayef Al-Rodhan</a>, an Honorary Fellow of St Antony’s College, University of Oxford and Head of the Geopolitics &amp; Global Futures Program at the Geneva Centre for Security Policy.</p>
<p>The winner of the prize will be announced later this fall.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/08/18/transdisciplinary-philosophy-book-prize-long-list-released/">Transdisciplinary Philosophy Book Prize Long List Released</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>